    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-08-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-08-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="194"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d194">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Sanford</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 140.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-08-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 8, 1864</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I submitted to the Secretary of the Navy your
                    despatch No. 200, marked <hi rend="italic">confidential,</hi> in which you
                    suggest the feasibility of enlisting foreigners in Belgium for our naval
                    service. In returning the despatch to this department he states that “the
                    proposed measure is both inexpedient and unnecessary, as we are now receiving
                    recruits in abundance.”</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry S. Sanford</hi>, Esq., &amp;<hi rend="italic"
                            >c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic"
                            >c</hi>.<hi rend="italic">, Brussels.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
